    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="letter">
                <pb n="1" facs="Edgeworth_NLS_42180_0000_06_07_page01.jpg"/>
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Edgeworthstown_IE"/><choice><orig>Edgeworth town</orig><reg>Edgeworthstown</reg></choice>
                        <date when="1111-06-07">June 7<hi rend="superscript">th</hi></date>
                        Cost £1386
                        Gross profit £150 -
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    Since I wrote to you last<lb/>
                    I have heard from my friend<lb/>
                    and yours the <persName ref="./Personography.xml#MarcJ1" cert="medium">Author of<lb/>
                    <title ref="./Workography.xml#Berth1">Bertha</title></persName> - and she answers<lb/>
                    that she is willing to <choice><orig>be=<lb/>
                    gin</orig><reg>begin</reg></choice> a new work for young<lb/>
                    people - of the same class<lb/>
                    of book as <title ref="./Workography.xml#Berth1">Bertha</title> at <del><unclear></unclear></del><lb/>
                    your desire but she can<lb/>
                    not bind herself as to<lb/>
                    time -<lb/>
                </p>
                <p>
                    She wishes however<lb/>
                    to know what your <choice><orig>con-<lb/>
                    venience</orig><reg>convenience</reg></choice> would be -<lb/>
                    About what time would<lb/>
                    you desire for your own<lb/>
                    sake that the <choice><orig>M<hi rend="superscript">s.</hi></orig><reg>Manuscript</reg></choice> (which<lb/>
                    is not yet begun) should<lb/>
                    be completed &amp; ready to<lb/>
                    put into your hands?<lb/>
                </p>
                <pb n="2" facs="Edgeworth_NLS_42180_0000_06_07_page02.jpg"/>
                <p>
                    As you encourage her<lb/>
                    to write more of the same<lb/>
                    sort as <title ref="./Workography.xml#Berth1">Bertha</title>, I suppose<lb/>
                    that the remuneration<lb/>
                    you propose to give will<lb/>
                    be at the same rate<lb/>
                    as for that happy latter<lb/>
                    work - But I must<lb/>
                    take nothing for granted<lb/>
                    in matters of business<lb/>
                    especially in <hi rend="underline">business</hi><lb/>
                    for a friend, therefore<lb/>
                    let me know exactly<lb/>
                    what you propose to<lb/>
                    do in this matter -<lb/>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    Yours sincerely<lb/>
                    <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeM1">Maria Edgeworth</persName><lb/>
                </closer>
             </div>
        </body>
        <back> </back>
    </text>
